1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:00,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:39,300
"Contrast"

3
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:42,700
(Episode 4: Just Pretend to Be Asleep)

4
00:01:42,780 --> 00:01:44,540
What was he trying to do just now?

5
00:01:45,890 --> 00:01:46,890
Akira...

6
00:01:51,830 --> 00:01:52,830
A kiss?

7
00:01:55,323 --> 00:01:56,323
No, I...

8
00:01:57,910 --> 00:01:58,910
But...

9
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,580
That's not the point...

10
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:45,700
Oh, Akira, did you finish the assignment?

11
00:02:45,850 --> 00:02:47,150
Yeah, I'm done.

12
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,160
That was fast.

13
00:02:48,610 --> 00:02:49,810
You're not finished yet?

14
00:02:49,820 --> 00:02:51,660
There's no way I could
finish it that quickly.

15
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:53,850
Whoa, that was close...

16
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:56,750
You okay?

17
00:02:59,170 --> 00:03:00,610
Watch where you're going.

18
00:03:02,980 --> 00:03:03,980
Yeah.

19
00:03:18,650 --> 00:03:20,430
I've been craving this so much.

20
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:23,120
And they were out of my usual
bacon bread today.

21
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:24,710
What kind of bread is that even?

22
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:25,959
Come on, I got curry bread too.

23
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:28,519
- Curry bread again? With apple juice?
- I have curry bread every day.

24
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,520
I'm seriously sick of it.

25
00:03:30,130 --> 00:03:31,130
What's up?

26
00:03:31,310 --> 00:03:32,310
Hmm?

27
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,480
It's nothing.

28
00:03:34,060 --> 00:03:37,290
You're just hoping some cute girl
will come confess to you, right?

29
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:39,260
- Right?
- Hey, where? Where is she?

30
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,640
That's not it.

31
00:03:40,860 --> 00:03:42,500
Makki, let's go.

32
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:44,050
See ya, Kanata.

33
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,680
- You're addicted to that curry bread.
- Hey, wait up!

34
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,310
Hey, by the way...

35
00:04:08,410 --> 00:04:11,020
Back then, weren't
our faces... really close?

36
00:04:12,490 --> 00:04:13,490
No, wait...

37
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:00,380
A kiss.

38
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,700
Were you trying to kiss me?

39
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:05,280
Huh?

40
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,120
I knew it.

41
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:10,840
You were pretending to be asleep.

42
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:12,850
What are you talking about?

43
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:15,790
Never mind then.

44
00:05:18,430 --> 00:05:19,430
Anyway...

45
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:22,070
You're not really the type
to make jokes like that, Akira.

46
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:23,590
Like what?

47
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:26,290
How do I put it...

48
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:31,520
You don't seem like the
type to talk about dirty stuff.

49
00:05:32,980 --> 00:05:33,980
Not really.

50
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:35,830
I talk about it.

51
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,780
With who?

52
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,520
You're asking me with who...

53
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,500
(Kanda Yoichi: Usual time?)

54
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,550
Who's Kanda?

55
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,900
A friend of my brother's.

56
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:54,340
You have a brother?

57
00:05:55,590 --> 00:05:56,590
How old is he?

58
00:05:58,330 --> 00:06:00,020
Around 23, I think.

59
00:06:01,650 --> 00:06:02,650
Wait, don't tell me...

60
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:04,970
You talk about dirty stuff with adults?

61
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:07,640
I guess so.

62
00:06:09,230 --> 00:06:11,000
Wait, Akira, are you...?

63
00:06:14,496 --> 00:06:17,336
Oh... never mind.

64
00:06:17,370 --> 00:06:18,120
No comment.

65
00:06:18,121 --> 00:06:19,620
Ah, don't say anything.

66
00:06:19,910 --> 00:06:21,110
You don't have to say it.

67
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,210
I didn't even give you an answer.

68
00:06:24,610 --> 00:06:26,190
Oh, right...

69
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:27,960
I guess so...

70
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:29,630
Yeah.

71
00:06:32,970 --> 00:06:34,170
I feel like...

72
00:06:35,330 --> 00:06:37,600
there's still so much I
don't know about you.

73
00:06:43,410 --> 00:06:44,510
Yeah.

74
00:06:49,190 --> 00:06:50,850
Makeup classes are exhausting.

75
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:52,680
Good work.

76
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:53,950
Want to walk home together?

77
00:06:53,950 --> 00:06:54,950
Sure.

78
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,910
He's really working hard.

79
00:06:58,980 --> 00:06:59,980
Yeah.

80
00:07:00,540 --> 00:07:02,770
That competitive streak
of his hasn't changed.

81
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,360
Mm-hmm.

82
00:07:05,380 --> 00:07:06,660
But I feel like...

83
00:07:07,190 --> 00:07:08,190
he's a bit different now.

84
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:09,630
Oh?

85
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:10,930
It's just...

86
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:13,690
How do I say it? He's
started to smile for real.

87
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:15,940
Yeah.

88
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:18,410
Oh, the day after tomorrow...

89
00:07:18,820 --> 00:07:20,549
I'm going to a late-night
movie with Kanata.

90
00:07:20,550 --> 00:07:21,566
Mizuki, do you want to come?

91
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:22,590
Oh, I'd love to.

92
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:24,739
OK, I'll book the seats then.

93
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:25,930
Thanks.

94
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,430
By the way...

95
00:07:55,431 --> 00:07:57,650
How's Hikaru doing lately?

96
00:07:58,880 --> 00:07:59,880
Oh...

97
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:00,920
My brother?

98
00:08:00,921 --> 00:08:03,450
He seemed fine when we
talked on the phone recently.

99
00:08:04,890 --> 00:08:05,890
I see.

100
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,030
You guys don't keep in touch?

101
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:12,680
Not as much as we used to.

102
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:18,280
Oh, it's not like we're on bad terms.

103
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,240
It's just that I'm working...

104
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:21,810
and he's still in grad school.

105
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,680
We just naturally talk less.

106
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:27,110
Right.

107
00:08:29,290 --> 00:08:31,610
Hard to believe how close we used to be.

108
00:08:41,050 --> 00:08:42,050
I'm back.

109
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,400
Excuse me.

110
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:46,030
This guy is your tutor.

111
00:08:47,130 --> 00:08:48,410
Tutor?

112
00:08:48,470 --> 00:08:50,430
Yeah, a friend from high school.

113
00:08:50,710 --> 00:08:52,330
He's been to our house plenty of times.

114
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:56,540
I thought you said you'd stop
cram school before summer...

115
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:59,630
Yoichi was looking for a part-time
job, so I thought it'd be perfect.

116
00:08:59,890 --> 00:09:01,820
Entrance exams are important, after all.

117
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:03,760
If you're okay with it, Akira.

118
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:06,800
I...

119
00:09:07,460 --> 00:09:08,660
I'd appreciate it.

120
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:10,140
Good.

121
00:09:11,090 --> 00:09:12,530
Looking forward to working with you.

122
00:09:27,350 --> 00:09:29,490
Do you like music too, Akira?

123
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:33,990
I... don't really know much about it.

124
00:09:35,330 --> 00:09:36,530
I see.

125
00:09:38,196 --> 00:09:39,706
My brother's the one into it.

126
00:09:40,820 --> 00:09:42,210
He listens to really trendy stuff.

127
00:09:44,210 --> 00:09:45,410
If you were to listen...

128
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,680
is there a specific kind of music you like?

129
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,960
Hmm...

130
00:09:51,910 --> 00:09:53,110
Maybe something loud.

131
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,100
Loud?

132
00:09:56,110 --> 00:09:57,110
Like...

133
00:09:57,190 --> 00:09:58,520
something that feels cathartic.

134
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,020
Something where...

135
00:10:01,830 --> 00:10:04,030
you don't have to think
about anything while listening.

136
00:10:04,570 --> 00:10:07,280
In that case, I have a few recommendations.

137
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:09,340
They're foreign bands.

138
00:10:09,490 --> 00:10:11,230
I have the CDs. I'll bring them next time.

139
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,590
Thanks.

140
00:10:16,460 --> 00:10:18,889
Hikaru didn't seem to like this style much.

141
00:10:18,890 --> 00:10:20,399
When the band came to Japan...

142
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,270
I ended up going by myself.

143
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:25,110
Oh, but we did go to a
music festival together.

144
00:10:26,580 --> 00:10:27,780
You guys are really close.

145
00:10:28,850 --> 00:10:30,210
Ever since my brother came back...

146
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:31,530
he's always been with you.

147
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:35,460
He's in Kansai now, so
it's hard to see each other.

148
00:10:37,770 --> 00:10:39,610
We weren't in the same
class in high school...

149
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:43,240
but I remember wondering
who was getting better grades than me.

150
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:44,820
Turns out it was him.

151
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:46,910
You're both pretty amazing.

152
00:10:47,790 --> 00:10:49,510
But your grades are good too, right, Akira?

153
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:52,450
They're okay.

154
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:56,640
But I've never been top of the class.

155
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:58,950
Hey, that's still impressive.

156
00:10:59,780 --> 00:11:02,680
Well... I guess.

157
00:11:07,660 --> 00:11:08,860
Compared to my brother...

158
00:11:10,460 --> 00:11:11,980
I really can't beat him at anything.

159
00:11:17,730 --> 00:11:20,070
Do you feel inferior?

160
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:34,310
If there's ever a day you don't need to
maintain that balance, make sure to tell me.

161
00:11:41,050 --> 00:11:42,050
Okay...

162
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:49,669
Come on, just tell me.

163
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:51,136
You actually have a girlfriend, don't you?

164
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:52,240
What school does she go to?

165
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:55,290
I'm not sure if I'd call
it "liking" someone...

166
00:11:56,540 --> 00:11:59,240
but there's someone
who kind of feels that way?

167
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:10,520
Senkawa-kun.

168
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,020
Thanks for the other day.

169
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:14,610
About Kanata.

170
00:12:15,020 --> 00:12:17,170
Oh... I didn't really do much.

171
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:21,090
I think Kanata has changed
since he met you.

172
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:22,390
Huh?

173
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,230
It's like he's back to how he was
when he took soccer seriously.

174
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,020
I'm really happy about it.

175
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:30,680
I see.

176
00:12:32,310 --> 00:12:33,310
So...

177
00:12:33,311 --> 00:12:34,560
thank you, really.

178
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,640
Sure.

179
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:37,660
If you don't mind...

180
00:12:37,661 --> 00:12:39,141
want to walk to the station together?

181
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:41,880
Oh, okay.

182
00:12:48,820 --> 00:12:49,920
Senkawa-kun.

183
00:12:49,980 --> 00:12:51,650
Do you study more after cram school?

184
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,160
Huh?

185
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:55,700
That person we ran into...
didn't you say he was your tutor?

186
00:12:56,370 --> 00:12:57,370
Oh...

187
00:12:58,610 --> 00:13:00,140
He's my tutor, but...

188
00:13:00,610 --> 00:13:02,170
he's actually a friend of my brother's.

189
00:13:02,417 --> 00:13:04,957
I see. So you have a brother.

190
00:13:05,270 --> 00:13:06,270
Yeah.

191
00:13:06,830 --> 00:13:08,570
He's at university in Kyoto right now.

192
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:11,080
Oh, Kyoto.

193
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:14,470
That's nice. I've never been there.

194
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,040
Um...

195
00:13:19,950 --> 00:13:20,950
Yeah?

196
00:13:21,290 --> 00:13:23,820
There's something I wanted to ask.

197
00:13:24,310 --> 00:13:25,310
What is it?

198
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:27,960
Kanata...

199
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:29,750
Hmm?

200
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:36,760
Sorry.

201
00:13:36,930 --> 00:13:37,930
Never mind.

202
00:13:56,610 --> 00:13:57,610
Yo.

203
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,360
Good work today.

204
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:04,850
Ah...

205
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:07,080
My muscles are killing me.

206
00:14:08,110 --> 00:14:09,110
How's the club?

207
00:14:09,740 --> 00:14:10,740
How's it going?

208
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,560
It's alright.

209
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:15,220
Are you having fun?

210
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:17,700
Yeah.

211
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,720
I mean, I am...

212
00:14:20,420 --> 00:14:21,840
but it's complicated.

213
00:14:23,490 --> 00:14:26,050
We didn't even make it past the
prelims for the next tournament.

214
00:14:27,210 --> 00:14:28,619
But I'm just a rookie...

215
00:14:28,620 --> 00:14:30,400
so I don't really have a right to complain.

216
00:14:31,970 --> 00:14:32,970
I see.

217
00:14:33,410 --> 00:14:36,140
Oh, but there are some
surprisingly good guys.

218
00:14:36,570 --> 00:14:38,290
Next year should be more interesting.

219
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:42,000
I guess that sounds a bit cocky.

220
00:14:43,410 --> 00:14:46,360
I'm just glad you're getting to play.

221
00:14:48,140 --> 00:14:49,140
Yeah.

222
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:05,290
Getting sleepy?

223
00:15:05,830 --> 00:15:06,830
Yeah.

224
00:15:07,770 --> 00:15:10,230
Think of it as a reward for working hard.

225
00:15:13,530 --> 00:15:14,690
What's that supposed to mean?

226
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,600
Hey.

227
00:15:35,860 --> 00:15:36,860
Hmm?

228
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:46,450
Akira...

229
00:15:51,550 --> 00:15:52,920
Have you ever kissed anyone?

230
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:58,240
What about you, Kanata?

231
00:15:59,490 --> 00:16:00,490
Ah.

232
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:02,260
That's not fair.

233
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:03,700
I asked first.

234
00:16:07,260 --> 00:16:08,260
I have.

235
00:16:10,780 --> 00:16:11,780
You?

236
00:16:20,890 --> 00:16:21,890
Me too.

237
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:32,710
Someone you were dating?

238
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:36,060
No.

239
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:38,680
Someone you liked?

240
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,700
Who knows...

241
00:16:44,290 --> 00:16:45,850
What? That's so vague.

242
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,200
What about you?

243
00:16:52,070 --> 00:16:53,070
Me...

244
00:16:56,610 --> 00:16:58,000
Like I said before...

245
00:16:58,970 --> 00:17:00,410
I didn't really care about anything.

246
00:17:02,140 --> 00:17:04,060
As long as I had something
to do besides soccer.

247
00:17:06,410 --> 00:17:11,250
So... I was just messing around.

248
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,540
Just to distract myself.

249
00:17:19,870 --> 00:17:21,070
Do you look down on me?

250
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,280
No.

251
00:17:26,830 --> 00:17:27,830
I see.

252
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:31,620
I thought you'd be more
serious about that stuff.

253
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,770
But I'm different now.

254
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:39,800
Oh.

255
00:17:41,490 --> 00:17:42,490
But...

256
00:17:43,606 --> 00:17:45,275
You knew I was pretending to be asleep...

257
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,620
and you still did that to me.

258
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,600
Huh?

259
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,200
At the festival.

260
00:17:51,470 --> 00:17:53,070
You got really close to my face.

261
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,100
Oh...

262
00:17:55,990 --> 00:17:56,990
Sorry.

263
00:17:57,370 --> 00:17:58,570
Stop messing with me.

264
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:03,260
I wasn't messing with you.

265
00:18:05,460 --> 00:18:06,460
It's just...

266
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,820
I was a little jealous of you.

267
00:18:11,020 --> 00:18:12,220
What do you mean?

268
00:18:14,780 --> 00:18:16,320
I thought if I got closer to you...

269
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:19,830
maybe I could become more like you.

270
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:22,660
You want to be like me?

271
00:18:23,350 --> 00:18:24,990
Better not. Your grades will tank.

272
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,810
Though you'd get better at soccer.

273
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:31,500
True.

274
00:18:32,770 --> 00:18:36,300
But the grades part is a bit...

275
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:40,410
We're different, and
that's a good thing, right?

276
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:44,069
Besides, even if we got that close...

277
00:18:44,070 --> 00:18:46,010
it wouldn't make you be like me.

278
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:49,420
You're right.

279
00:18:51,790 --> 00:18:53,470
You're changing the subject, aren't you?

280
00:19:02,460 --> 00:19:05,380
Is that not allowed?

281
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:11,950
No.

282
00:19:16,470 --> 00:19:20,580
This time... you should
pretend to be asleep too.

283
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:10,000
Crap, I gotta go.

284
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:12,889
Hey, we're all going to a movie today.

285
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:13,890
You want to come, Akira?

286
00:20:15,070 --> 00:20:15,900
Sorry.

287
00:20:15,901 --> 00:20:17,661
- I'm seeing my brother today...
- Oh, I see.

288
00:20:17,770 --> 00:20:18,770
See you next time, then.

289
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,440
What's wrong?

290
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:36,160
Huh?

291
00:20:37,380 --> 00:20:38,930
Your face is bright red.

292
00:20:40,850 --> 00:20:41,850
I'm almost late.

293
00:20:42,050 --> 00:20:43,050
That's why I was running.

294
00:20:57,180 --> 00:20:58,180
Okay.

295
00:20:58,650 --> 00:20:59,850
Now then.

296
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:02,950
This poem describes the joy of
seeing a loved one in a dream...

297
00:21:03,090 --> 00:21:06,470
and the sadness of waking up.

298
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,690
Wanting to see the person
you love, even in a dream...

299
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:15,079
To care for someone that much...

300
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:16,640
is actually a beautiful thing.

301
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:26,850
Sorry I'm late.

302
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:27,640
No worries.

303
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:29,420
I was just killing time
around here anyway.

304
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:31,490
By the way, where's Jun?

305
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:33,520
Oh, he messaged saying he'll be a bit late.

306
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:36,000
And he's the one who insisted we go today.

307
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:38,470
Oh.

308
00:21:38,490 --> 00:21:40,210
Should we see if Senkawa-kun wants to join?

309
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:42,026
If he just finished cram school...

310
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:43,459
he should still be around here.

311
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:44,460
No need.

312
00:21:47,550 --> 00:21:49,200
He has plans today.

313
00:21:49,820 --> 00:21:51,169
Something with his brother.

314
00:21:51,170 --> 00:21:52,170
Huh?

315
00:21:52,830 --> 00:21:54,100
I heard Akira has a brother.

316
00:21:54,610 --> 00:21:56,160
Yeah, I know.

317
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:58,560
We talked about it on the
way back from cram school.

318
00:21:58,800 --> 00:21:59,960
Oh, really?

319
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:01,760
But...

320
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:04,980
I heard his brother is
at university in Kyoto.

321
00:22:05,670 --> 00:22:06,670
Wait, what?

322
00:22:07,370 --> 00:22:10,370
I mean, maybe he's back for a visit.

323
00:22:12,270 --> 00:22:13,270
I guess.

324
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:17,420
How do I put this...

325
00:22:36,220 --> 00:22:37,220
Akira...?

326
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:28,896
(Next Episode)
Let's have a training camp.

327
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:30,450
Are you even trying to study?

328
00:23:31,030 --> 00:23:32,030
Wow, amazing.

329
00:23:32,600 --> 00:23:34,200
Wait, only mine has brakes!

330
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,720
Kanata.

331
00:23:38,850 --> 00:23:40,240
Why did you kiss me?
